Que 1: Introduction to for and while loops
for loop → Used when you know the number of iterations
It is mainly used to iterate over a sequence (like list, range, string, etc.)

for loops iterate over a collection of items, such as list or dict, and run a block of code with each element from
the collection.
range is a function that returns a series of numbers under an iterable form, thus it can be used in for loops:

while Loop : A while loop will cause the loop statements to be executed until the loop condition is falsey.


Que:2 How loops work in Python.
Loop : A loop keeps running a block of code again and again
It stops only when a condition becomes false or the sequence ends

How Loops Work (Step-by-Step)

Think like this:
Start
Check condition / get next item
Run the code
Repeat
Stop when done

Start → Condition Check → Execute Code → Update → Repeat → Stop

